<div id="review_1926444525" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1926444525" />
    <a title="Sue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1031749-sue"><img alt="Sue" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1926444525?book_show_action=true">Jun 20, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sue" href="/user/show/1031749-sue">Sue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1926444525" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6068183938484207708">I liked this book yet it made me sad - there was so much horror during the Holocaust and I have a hard time with the way people were treated. I am amazed that this man and his brothers survived and lived lives without hate. We all can learn a lot from this and treat others with respect and dignity even if we don&apos;t agree with them. I know the above wasn&apos;t about the book but that was what I came away with, which is a good reason to read the book.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText6068183938484207708" style="display:none">I liked this book yet it made me sad - there was so much horror during the Holocaust and I have a hard time with the way people were treated. I am amazed that this man and his brothers survived and lived lives without hate. We all can learn a lot from this and treat others with respect and dignity even if we don't agree with them. I know the above wasn't about the book but that was what I came away with, which is a good reason to read the book.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6068183938484207708" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


