<div id="review_2553403894" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2553403894" />
    <a title="Deborah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30372157-deborah"><img alt="Deborah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617108004p2/30372157.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2553403894?book_show_action=true">Oct 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deborah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deborah" href="/user/show/30372157-deborah">Deborah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780762782307" href="/book/show/23337457-trusting-calvin">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2553403894" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5479601689191768522">This book paired my keen interest in the holocaust and dogs. Max Edelman was a courageous man who survived a concentration camp and overcame his intense fear of dogs, which was ignited by a Nazi&apos;s German Shepherd tearing apart a man standing next to him in the camp. Max&apos;s guide dogs gradually helped him deal with the trauma of internment and share his war time experiences with countless people. Peters did a good job of telling Max&apos;s story.</span>
  <span id="freeText5479601689191768522" style="display:none">This book paired my keen interest in the holocaust and dogs. Max Edelman was a courageous man who survived a concentration camp and overcame his intense fear of dogs, which was ignited by a Nazi's German Shepherd tearing apart a man standing next to him in the camp. Max's guide dogs gradually helped him deal with the trauma of internment and share his war time experiences with countless people. Peters did a good job of telling Max's story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5479601689191768522" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


